  "body": "**getCommitteeAssignment()**\r\n\r\nI don't have any profile to show but this function in called inside a loop so it totals 4 nested loops\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/e669010b787965883de32561d5d13064b916cedc/packages/beacon-state-transition/src/fast/util/epochContext.ts#L267-L271\r\n\r\nWhen a beacon node is attached to many validators it may be an issue.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nIs it worth it to find a more efficient strategy? Lighthouse seems to loop only once per validator index, checking inclusion in the nth_committee range\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/3a24ca5f14c6e6d6612fd43eca82aa0c1e6aba16/consensus/types/src/beacon_state/committee_cache.rs#L166",
